@startuml
title Viaverse Request Creation — Sequence Diagram

actor Requester
participant "KMP / Web Client" as Client
participant "API Gateway / App BFF" as BFF
participant "marketplace-service" as Marketplace
participant "AI Provider Adapter" as AI
participant "media-service" as Media
participant "MapProvider" as Maps
database "PostgreSQL" as DB
queue "Outbox / Kafka" as Kafka

Requester -> Client : open Create / request service
Client -> BFF : POST /service-requests draft
BFF -> Marketplace : createDraft(command)
Marketplace -> DB : insert ServiceRequest(DRAFT)

Client -> BFF : POST /ai/request-suggestions
BFF -> AI : suggest category/budget
AI --> BFF : suggestions
BFF --> Client : editable suggestions

Client -> BFF : POST /media/upload-sessions
BFF -> Media : createUploadSession
Media -> DB : store MediaAsset(PENDING)
Media --> BFF : presigned URL + mediaId
BFF --> Client : upload info

Client -> BFF : PATCH draft with fields/media refs
BFF -> Marketplace : updateDraft(command)
Marketplace -> Maps : geocode / area normalize
Marketplace -> DB : update draft

Client -> BFF : POST /service-requests/{id}/publish
BFF -> Marketplace : publishRequest(command)
Marketplace -> DB : validate + set PUBLISHED + insert outbox
Marketplace -> Kafka : ServiceRequestPublished
Marketplace -> Kafka : MatchingRequested
Marketplace --> BFF : published request
BFF --> Client : success

note over Marketplace
Publish transaction:
- validate REQUEST_WORK capability
- validate required fields
- set status PUBLISHED
- write outbox events
end note
@enduml
